column5: Well everyone, I am so excited I am trying to type this properly but I had to give you all an incredible news, My brother-in-law just called me now, and I am very proud to say I am now the aunt of a wonderful niece! My sister had her new daughter at 5:00 this evening! She weighed in at 5 lbs 11 oz and is very healthy! Her name is Dianna. Well now I can relax and count all the blessings that I have. I could have not asked for a better Christmas gift!  I would like to take the time to thank everyone here for their kind words and incredible support that you have shown me and my family. Thank you very much, you guys are the BEST!
Congrats FG72!!!  Nice little present at this time of year!  Just remember when she grows up she'll want two presents at this time of year!!  Congrats again and hope everyone is doing well.
Thank you very much HearingFish! Tell me about it, I already know that, she will be a expensive little girl to buy for!   Mom and baby are doing just great! Merry Christmas to you and your family!
Congrats Fishergirl, what a great gift.  Hope momma and baby are doing well.  Your brother in law is having quite the leave, what great timing.

Thank you very much steve paul! Mommy and baby are doing great. I am just sitting here trying to stop from tearing up! I am so glad that he could be home to be there for the birth of his first child, he missed everything else. He will never forget this leave!  Thanks TJ! Merry Christmas!
Congrats!!!  blyght and I are very happy for you and your now bigger family!! It's so great that dad could be here to see it.  Merry Christmas!!!
Thanks ccmt and blyght!!  I am so happy, I can barely contain it! Yeah I am glad that he could be there for the birth since he missed everything else! Merry Christmas to you, Carole and the girls!
CONGRATULATIONS TO THE NEW AUNT A MERRY CHRISTMAS INDEED

Thank you very much Biteme! I just recieved some pictures of the little bundle and I will post one soon.  I will never forget this xmas, it has been one of a kind, that's for sure!  Merry Christmas Biteme!
Congrats, that is great news!  Mike
Great news fishergirl. I hope you enjoy the Holiday Season.
